A critical security incident involving exploitation of a Samba vulnerability was detected. The attacker successfully gained unauthorized access to the system using a known exploit. Wazuh generated alerts indicating suspicious activity from the attacker’s IP. Immediate containment actions were taken, including isolating the affected system and blocking the attacker’s IP address. The activity aligns with MITRE ATT&CK technique T1210 (Exploitation of Remote Services). Due to the severity and risk of lateral movement, the incident is escalated to Tier 2 for detailed forensic analysis, patch validation, and full impact assessment.
